
[1]centaur

   CENTAUR, n.

   1. In mythology, a fabulous being, supposed to be half man and half
   horse. It has been supposed that this fancied monster originated among
   the Lapithae, a tribe in Thessaly, who first invented the art of
   breaking horses. But the origin of the fable and of the name is
   doubtful.

   2. Part of a southern constellation, in form of a centaur, usually
   joined with the wolf, containing thirty-five stars; the archer.
